content:
I'm trying to install auto-sklearn on my Ubuntu 16.04.2 operating system using the command `pip install auto-sklearn`. However, I'm receiving an error during the installation process. The error message I'm receiving is:

```
Command "/usr/bin/python3.5 -u -c "
    import setuptools, tokenize;
    __file__='/tmp/pip-build-tl8y2tfg/psutil/setup.py';
    f=getattr(tokenize, 'open', open)(__file__);
    code=f.read().replace('\r\n', '\n');
    f.close();
    exec(compile(code, __file__, 'exec'))
"install 
    --record /tmp/pip-7t8rbku0-record/install-record.txt 
    --single-version-externally-managed --compile" 
failed with error code 1 in /tmp/pip-build-tl8y2tfg/psutil/
```

I've followed the steps from the installation manual provided in the auto-sklearn documentation and also tried the commands from a similar issue on Stack Overflow, but neither of these have resolved my problem. Notably, there are no files or directories that begin with "pip-" present in my `/tmp/` directory. How can I successfully install auto-sklearn?
